# Interaction polish

See also: **`accessibility.mdc`**, **`error-handling.mdc`**, **`async-ui.mdc`**, **`design-tokens.mdc`**, **`delight-ux.mdc`**. Index: [`skills/SKILL.md`](../../skills/SKILL.md).

Premium UIs acknowledge **every action immediately** (target under 100ms when possible). This rule covers **motion, feedback, keyboard, and selection** — not colors or tokens (`design-tokens.mdc`).

**Data surface states** (loading / empty / error / ready) → **`error-handling.mdc`**. **Optimistic UI & races** → **`async-ui.mdc`**. **Offline & drafts** → **`offline-reconnect.mdc`**, **`forms-and-drafts.mdc`**. **Empty/error copy** → **`copy/ui-microcopy.mdc`**.

## Philosophy

Acknowledge clicks, submits, toggles, and navigation — via focus move, loading on control, optimistic update, or state change. Never leave an action unacknowledged.

If work may exceed **~300ms**, show skeleton, progress, or optimistic state — never silent wait.

## State-driven controls

For **data surfaces**, follow **`error-handling.mdc`**. For **controls**, define: idle, hover, pressed, loading, disabled, success on buttons; focus/error on inputs; hover/focus/selected on rows. Use shadcn variants + `aria-*`.

## Micro-feedback

| Action | Feedback |
| ------ | -------- |
| Save | Brief success or checkmark |
| Copy | “Copied” toast or inline |
| Submit | Loading → success/error on control |
| Delete | Animate out or undo toast |

Users should never wonder: “Did it work?”

## Selection

Hover, focus, and selected states on every selectable element. Selection **not color alone** — background, border/ring, icon/weight, `aria-selected`.

## Motion

Every animation answers: **what changed? why? where did it go?**

- Prefer **`transform` and `opacity`** — not width/height/shadow on large lists.
- Preserve spatial memory — animate moves, don’t teleport content.
- Expand/collapse: grid `0fr`/`1fr` — not `max-height` hacks.
- **Metric animation** only on high-signal KPIs — not every table cell.
- Respect **`prefers-reduced-motion`** — global CSS in `index.css`; no decorative loops.

## Progressive rendering & layout stability

Render shell first; load regions independently — never block full page on slowest query (`error-handling.mdc`). Reserve space with skeletons matching final dimensions; avoid layout jump when data arrives.

## Skeletons

Prefer skeleton matching layout over lone page spinner. Inline refresh: stale content + subtle progress. Button actions: loading state on the control.

## Undo over confirm

Reversible actions → act + **undo toast**. Confirm dialogs only for destructive/irreversible/high-stakes.

## Contextual & progressive disclosure

Reveal row actions on hover/selection/focus. Essential controls first; advanced behind expand/tabs/“More”.

## Density (desktop dashboards)

Compact tables and purposeful padding on data-heavy screens — not oversized marketing-style cards on admin surfaces.

## Typography anti-patterns (AI slop)

Avoid **uppercase tracked micro-labels** on every section:

```tsx
// Bad
<p className="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-muted-foreground">Overview</p>
// Good
<p className="text-sm font-medium text-foreground">Overview</p>
```

## Keyboard & focus

- **Enter** confirms; **Esc** closes overlays; **Tab** logical order; arrows in lists/menus/tabs.
- After create → focus new item field; after close modal → return to trigger; after delete → next row or container.
- Command palette (`Cmd+K`) for search-heavy apps — but never hide **critical** flows behind shortcuts alone.

## Consistency

Similar components must behave the same across lists, forms, modals, and empty states.

## Checklist

- [ ] Actions acknowledged immediately; slow work shows progress/skeleton/optimistic state.
- [ ] Page regions render progressively; layouts stable when data arrives.
- [ ] Hover, focus, pressed, disabled, loading defined on composed UI.
- [ ] Selection obvious without color alone.
- [ ] Motion has intent; `prefers-reduced-motion` respected.
- [ ] No uppercase tracking-widest eyebrows on every section.
- [ ] Keyboard path exists; focus moves sensibly after actions.
- [ ] Reversible deletes use undo where appropriate.
- [ ] Primitives use shadcn preset — no conflicting custom press/hover overrides.
